caption.body: In 1970, PSA (Pacific Southwest Airlines) introduced eye-catching pink and apricot flight attendant uniforms and showcased them on their ticket jackets. Most airlines have phased out ticket jackets, and they have become collectors’ items. Do you remember ticket jackets? “Catch Our Style” is on display, pre-security, in the Aviation Museum and Library in the International Terminal. The Aviation Museum and Library is open from Sunday through Friday, 10am to 4:30pm or check out our online exhibition at: http://www.flysfo.com/museum/exhibitions/catch-our-style-california-regional-airlines-1950s%E2%80%931980s
